{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Create power to permanently remove vehicles from dangerous/undocumented drivers",
        "additional_details": "Thousands are maimed or killed every year by drunk, speeding, unlicensed and uninsured drivers. We think bans don't work, fines don't work, and unpaid work orders don't work. Remove their cars and we believe behaviour will change. Losing your car, your status symbol, will hurt. The more you can afford, the more expensive the car will be, so the pain will be relative but fair. Give the Police some real support and protect the public.",
        "background": "Enact a Law to give Magistrates and Police powers to remove vehicles permanently from those not entitled to be on the road or whose actions on the road endanger the general public. Those vehicles would then be crushed or sold (if viable) and the value returned to Police services and victim funds",
